// ── Native elementwise FFI (hxblas_wrapper.c extension block) ──────
// ROOT CAUSE FIX for blocker #3 in training_speed_ceilings.json:
// scalar deref_f32/write_f32 loops in the nnt_* functions below compiled
// to boxed-int arithmetic (hexa_mul/hexa_add per element), dominating
// 60-80% of step time at d>=128. These C functions execute the same math
// with native float* pointers — one FFI call per WHOLE TENSOR instead
// of per element. On Apple Silicon clang -O3 auto-vectorises these into
// NEON SIMD; on Linux they vectorise via SSE/AVX.
@link("/Users/ghost/Dev/anima/training/build/libhxblas.dylib")
